reviewText: It's time for another retro rasslin review for WCW's 1st ever Fall Brawl. An event that replaces Wrestle War. Now I will tell what happended since Beach Blast. On The August 14th episode of WCW Saturday Night Harley Race was mad that Ric Flair wasn't on the upcoming Clash Of Champions to wrestle. So he got involved in a little side feud to help Sting. He decided to team up with Sting at Clash Of The Champions 24 to face The Colassal Kongs 1 of the worst tag teams ever. It was a squash as well at this Clash The main event for Fall Brawl was made Sting The British Bulldog Dustin Rhodes & a mystery partner vs Vader Sid Vicious & Harlem Heat. On a Flair For The Gold some classic wrestle crap happend Fred Ottman known as Tugboat crashed through a wall & fell on his face wearing a Storm Trooper helmet. Which was spray painted too. I have heard earlier in the day that the stunt worked fine but David Crockett put a board there. Vader also got a rematch against Vader's WCW World Heavyweight Championship on this Clash. Vader retained with the help of Harley Race. On The August 21st episode of WCW Saturday Night Sting recieeved a shot at The NWA World Heavyweight Championship. Ric Flair & Sting had a 40 or 50 minute classic on free TV. Sid Vicious interfered & cost Sting the match he was counted out. On The September 18th episode of WCW Saturday Night Sting was wrestling Stevie Ray Booker T came in & cost him the match. Dustin Rhodes came into help but was beat up by Harlem Heat Booker T dropped knee from the top rope on to his throat. Later on an injured Rhodes teamed with Flair to help him Rhodes took a beating Harlem Heat interfered Sting came down The Shockmaster came down. The 2 War Games teams brawled to close the show. On The August 28th episode of WCW Saturday Night Ric Flair had Ric Rude as a guest on A Flair For The Gold. Rude wanted Fifi Rude kissed her she smacked him. Then Rude took The NWA World Championship belt & hit Flair in the back of the head & gave him a Rude Awakening on floor. He told Fifi "You're a gold digger & he's got the belt & when Mr 10 times World Champion comes to tell him that the belts coming with me & so are you!" Flair agreed & put The NWA World title on the line for Fall Brawl. Rude later said on this episode that he will make Ric Flair use all the tricks in his bag until the bag is empty & he is champion. Only we thougth this was going to be for The NWA World Championship. The NWA was mad that when Windham was champion & Flair now that he had there World title wasn't wrestling in there promotions & the fact that Rude was filmed already wearing the belt at The Double D tapings was enough to make The NWA withdraw from WCW & on September 1st 1993 WCW withdrew from The NWA. So for this show I will call the title just The World Heavyweight Championship only. On The September 4th episode of WCW Saturday Night Flair teamed up with Sting & The British Bulldog to face Sid Vicious & Harlem Heat. Rude came out & attacked Flair with a 2X4 that Flair brought with him to ringside. There was also a series of  3 matches going on with Rude & Dustin Rhodes over The WCW United States Championship. Rude won the 1st match the 2nd went to Dustin Rhodes & on The September 11th episode of WCW Saturday Night the 3rd match went to Dustin The referee was knocked out Rude went for a steel chair Flair stopped him & Rhodes got the fall to finally decide The US title. At The Clash Of Champions 24 Ricky Steamboat defeated Paul Orndorff to win The WCW Televison Championship. On The September 4th episode of WCW Saturday Night Steven Regal got a shot for The TV title at Fall Brawl. On The September 18th episode of WCW Saturday Night Paul Orndorff after winning a match went & beat up the jobber he beat some more. Steamboat came out to make the save where Steve Regal took Sir William's umbrella & beat Steamboat all over with it. At Clash Of The Champions 24 Arn Anderson & Paul Roma defeated The Hollywood Blondes to win The NWA_WCW World Tag Team Championship. For some reason The Nasty Boys who returned after 3 years got1st crack at Anderson & Roma for The WCW World Tag Team Championship. Been awhile since I called it just The WCW World Tag Team titles. Cactus Jack returned at Clash Of The Champions 24 & jumped Vader Harley Race hired Yoshi Kwan to put Cactus Jack out. The Road Warriors returned at Clash Of The Champions 24. If you like or dislike me telling the backstory to what lead up to the main feuds going into each Pay Per View then comment me. I love telling the backstory for each show. The buyrate was an 0.46.Date September 19, 1993Attendance 6,000Venue Astro arenaThe opening was kind of cool.WCW World Television ChampionshipSteven Regal with Sir William Def Champion Ricky Steamboat to win the title ****Sir William hit Steamboat with an umbrellaEric Bischoff interviewed The Nasty Boys Jerry Sags said they have a suprise. Knobs said you're looking at the next World Tag Team Champions.Charlie Norris Def Big Sky aka Nitron aka The Worst Michael Myers * just a poor match. The fans didn't care 1 bit.Scott Dunlap interviewed The British Bulldog2 Cold Scorpio & Marcus Alexander Bagwell Def Paul Orndorff & The Equalizer * & 3 quarters of a star2 Cold said that they want the tag titles before the match. Pretty boring match. Sad caus Scorpio is great Bagwell is alright in the ring & Orndorff is a great performer. Orndorff & The Equalizer beat 2 Cold & Bagwell up after they lost.Eric Bischoff interviewed Steven Regal Sir William said that tomarrow morning they will be highly commended by The Queen. Bischoff called Regal out for his cheating Regal said I'm a Lord & a Gentleman if you can't trust me who can you trust. Bischoff said absolutley no one.Ice Train Def Shanghai Pierce with Tex DUD a s  h  i  t match. Choo choo oh yeah Ice Train Jesse Ventrua said that Tex & Shanghai rank up with Ann Rich  a  r  d  s as the most popular people from Texas 3rd was Lee H  a  r  v  e  yOs  w  a  l  d.  A match that I couldn't wait to be over.Promo for The Halloween Havoc Pay Per ViewWCW World Tag Team ChampionshipThe Nasty Boy with Missy Hyatt Def Champions Arn Anderson & Paul Roma ** & quarter of a star to win the titles.WTF was WCW thinking taking the most over & only woman in the comapny besides Fifi but she wasn't in WCW as long as  Missy was. & turn her heel. Roma is suprisingly over. This match was half decent but boring at the same time. 26 minutes I think. I defended The Arn & Roma Hollywood Blondes match at Beach Blast cause Arn is a great wrestler Austin & Pillman could work & that covered up Roma's average wrestling ability. The Nasty Boys can't work 25 30 minute matches. Roma did a better job wrestling than The Nasty Boys.The crowd was great Jesse's commentary was good too.Jesse Ventrua interviewed The Nasty Boys & Missy Hyatt. They all said that The 4 Horsemen are dead. Missy said that this was revenge against Ric Flair & Arn Anderson.Video package for Cactus Jack is shown & it was pretty goodCactus Jack Def Yoshi Kwan with Harley Race half a star in a poor match.  Cactus Jack got the bag back & he challenged Vader.They recap The Rude, Flair match.Finally something awesomeWorld Heavyweight ChampionshipRick Rude Def Champion Ric Flair with Ffif *****Michael Bufffer said that Rude was making his 1st challenge for The World title. Buffer said that before the match Ric Flair would like to say a few words well he handed the mic to Rude. Rude  had cloth that had Flair on it it said please don't hit me & he said that not only will I take your World title but I'm going to take your woman his tights have Fifi airbrushed on them. This is also the match where Jesse Ventura's mic was cut. I know I'm in the minority but this match is a forgotten classic. The Referee was distracted by Fifi & Rude hit Flair with some Knucks to get the win.War Games The Mathc BEYOND!StingThe Brithish BulldogDustin Rhodes& The ShockmasterDefVaderSid ViciousBooker T& Stevie Raywith Colonel Parker & Harley RaceDustin Rhodes started for Sting's teamVader started for The Race-Parker teamStevie Ray went in 2nd for The Race-Parker teamSting went in 2nd for his teamSid Vicious went in 3rd for The Race-Parker teamThe British Bulldog went in 3rd for Sting's teamBooker T went in last for The Race- Parker teamThe Shockmaster went in last for Sting's teamThe Shockmaster made Booker T submit to a bear hug. ** & a quarter of a star.It's halfway decent but this is War Games it should be to the standard this was lame. The heels yelling at the end was entertaining though. Not a great PPV. The best matches was Regal vs Steamboat with Regal winning The TV title. Rick Rude winning The World title defeating Flair in a very underrated match was awesome. 2 forgotten matches The Nasty Boys vs Anderson & Roma while being a half decent match didn't need to be 26 minutes. The underrcard was bad it need a few more 2 star matches & I would've given it a higher rating. 7 & half is probably being too generous. I know 411 mania said this was worse than The Great American Bash 91. The Great American Bash is such a horrid show with bad match after bad match atleast this had a 4 star match & a 5 star match. The Wretling Observer said this was the worst show of 93 how about Wrestlemania IX  or Summerslam 93 a show where they build a guy up so much but don't give him the title.  My next retro rasslin review will be Halloween Havoc 1993.
summary: 2  forgotten classic matches but the rest is completly mediocre 7.5/10 maybe I'm being too nice
Title: WCW Fall Brawl 1993 VHS

reviewText: The Crusierweight title between Elix Skipper & Kwee Wee was not great but pretty good and the same goes the 6 man tag team match between The Misfits In Action(Cpl.Cajun,Lt.Loco & Sgt.AWOL) & 3 Count(Shannon Moore,Evan Karagias & Shane Helms). The First Blood/Chain match between The Harris Brothers(Don & Ron) & Kronik(Brian Adams & Bryan Clark) was a pretty good/solid brawl. The US Title match between Lance Storm & General Rection was so-so at best. The 14 person tag team elimination match was slow & long "at best" and the same goes for the mixed Scaffold team match between the team of Shane Douglas & Torrie Wilson against the team of Billi Kidman & Madusa. The Sting-Vampiro-Great Muta 3 way dance was pretty much a 2-on-1 hanicap match. The Mike Awesome-Jeff Jarrett Bunkhouse Brawl was almost as good as a match in ECW back in the 1990's and could have done better without so many people interfering. The Scott Steinter-Goldberg No-DQ match was an average WCW brawl at best. The Steel cage match for the world title between Booker T & Kevin Nash while not a bad bout,it could have done better. I give this PPV a 7 out of 10.
Title: WCW Fall Brawl 1993 VHS

reviewText: I'm not a big wcw fan but I did like this event. The Goldberg and Steiner match was the best match on this tape. The Pittsburgh Plunge Match wasn't good at all!  The falls were so fake with mudusa landing on some kind of cushon, I know it is all fake but that is the worst fall I have seen. Other then this one match this is event is worth watching.
Title: WCW Fall Brawl 1993 VHS

reviewText: 1.) WCW Cruiserweight Championship Match: Kwee Wee w/Paisley vs Elix Skipper w/Major GunnsA decent Cruiserweight match to open the show with Elix Skipper, representing Team Canada putting his title on the line against Kwee Wee. 1 or 2 botched moves here and there. Natural Born Thrillers' Mike Sanders interferes near the end of the match and attacks Kwee Wee with a kendo stick. Elix takes advantage and hits the Overdrive on Kwee Wee to retain the title. Not the best of matches to open a PPV_____________________________________________________________________________________________________2.) 3 Count (Shannon Moore, Evan Karagias, and Shane Helms) vs The Misfits In Action (Cpl. Cajun, Lt. Loco, and Sgt. AWOL)A match featuring 2 of WCW's goofiest Tag Teams. A solid and fun Tag Team match with a lot of high flying action from both teams, especially 3 Count. Many people may have hated 3 Count, but they were very talented and exciting to watch in the ring. Cpl Cajun gets the pinfall win for his team with a Whiplash 2000 on Shane Helms_____________________________________________________________________________________________________3.) First Blood Chain Match: The Harris Brothers vs KronikThis was a Tornado Tag Team match, to try and make the match more interesting to watch but it didn't work. Nothing exciting really going on in this match. The referee gets knocked down towards the end. Ron Harris bleeds first but the referee never saw it when he came to. Brian Adams gets nailed with a baseball bat that looks like its wrapped in barbed wire before getting pummeled with a chain. The referee sees Brian bleeding and rings the bell. Harris Brothers win this lackluster match_____________________________________________________________________________________________________General Rection cuts a patriotic pre-match promo on Lance Storm with Hacksaw Jim Duggan by his side_____________________________________________________________________________________________________4.) WCW US Championship Match: Lance Storm (c) w/Major Gunns vs General Rection  (Outside Enforcer: Hacksaw Jim Duggan)Before the match, Storm cuts a great heel promo about how great Canada is. Great promo but unfortunately, Storm never had the charisma to truly get his promos where they could've been. Another seemingly lackluster match. The only noteworthy thing about this match was Duggan's heel turn and joining Team Canada, which probably could've been seen a mile away, considering how notorious WCW was for turning superstars heel. Duggan knocks out General Rection with the 2x4 while the referee's back is turned and Storm applies the Maple Leaf on a ko'd Rection for the win. MIA comes out to try and save General Rection at the end but  they all get beat down by Hacksaw._____________________________________________________________________________________________________5.) Elimination Tag Team Match: Natural Born Thrillers (Mark Jindrak, Sean O'Haire, Chuck Palumbo, Shawn Stasiak, Reno, Johnny the Bull Stamboli, and Mike Sanders) vs Filthy Animals (Disco Inferno, Rey Mysterio, Juventud Guerrera, and Konnan w/Tygress),Vito, and Paul OrndorffWhat possessed WCW to bring Paul Orndorff on-screen for a match? This PPV was in September 2000 and Orndorff hadn't been relevant since the 80s. The match itself was an interesting and fun one to watch, but making Orndorff a part of this match brought it down a bit. Referee Charles Robinson stops the match after Orndorff injures his neck with his own piledriver on Jindrak. See? Putting him in the match was a bad idea. So basically the match goes to a no contest because of Orndorff's injury. Lame way for the match to end_____________________________________________________________________________________________________A backstage pre-match interview with Billy Kidman and Madusa. Kidman promises to throw Shane Douglas off the scaffold. Madusa goes crazy and threatens to do the same to Torrie_____________________________________________________________________________________________________6.) Tag Team Scaffold Match: Torrie Wilson and Shane Douglas vs Madusa and Billy KidmanDouglas cuts a promo before Kidman and Madusa come out but I was too busy looking at Torrie to pay attention to what he was saying. This match goes nowhere. Ends with Torrie getting a low blow in on Kidman and Douglas tossing Kidman off the top of the scaffold. Torrie and Douglas climb down the ladder to win the match_____________________________________________________________________________________________________Sting is backstage cutting a pre-match promo on Dark Carnival when he's attacked from behind by Jeff Jarrett for no apparent reason. Then we're shown a weird recorded segment of Mike Tenay visiting David Flair's house who asks him about the wedding where he was left at the altar by Stacy Keibler and having Stacy admit to him that he wasn't the father of her baby. David is depressed and losing his mind as his place is covered in trash, newspapers, and pizza. He's paranoid and runs outside and attacks the mailman, thinking he's the father of Stacy's baby. In case you don't know, the original route for this storyline was for Ric Flair to be revealed as the father. At one point, Vince Russo even considered making himself the father. Thank goodness this storyline never went anywhere_____________________________________________________________________________________________________7.) Vampiro vs Great Muta vs StingThe ICP clowns take over the commentary desk and commentate with Mark Madden for duration of the match. This was a rather short match that saw Muta and Vampiro work over Sting for most of this short bout. In the end, Sting hits Muta with his bat and hits the Scorpion Death Drop on him for the win. Muta gets attacked by Dark Carnival after the match and Sting makes the save_____________________________________________________________________________________________________Mike Awesome gets off of his 70s bus and tries to pick up on Pamela Paulshock and introduces Gary Coleman as his special guest_____________________________________________________________________________________________________8.) Bunkhouse Brawl: Jeff Jarrett vs Mike AwesomeNot too bad of a hardcore type match that gets close to 10 minutes. Near the end, after one too many insults, the Buffalo Bills hit the ring and attack Jarrett. Follow this up with an interference and attack from Gary Coleman and an another interference from Sting who interferes and hits the Scorpion Death Drop on Jarrett. After all this Awesome picks up the scraps and pins Jarrett for the win. The match started off good but got pretty ridiculous at the end with all the interferences_____________________________________________________________________________________________________9.) No Disqualifications: Goldberg vs Scott SteinerThe build-up for this match was great. After Goldberg Jackhammered Steiner's freak, Midajah through a table, Scott got revenge by attacking Goldberg's girlfriend and placing her in the Steiner Recliner. Steiner had to wrestle with a mask due to Goldberg supposedly injuring his face with a lead pipe, leading up to the PPV. Great, solid, and exciting No DQ match to view. With Goldberg and Steiner being brutal wrestlers, this one was bound to be...well....brutal! Goldberg flat out dominates Steiner for the first few minutes of the match but Steiner fights back with a steel chair, busting Goldberg open. Midajah comes to the ring with a lead pipe. Russo interferes and attacks Goldberg with a pipe of his own. Midajah and Russo both attack Goldberg with pipes but Goldberg kicks out of Steiner's pin following the attacks. In the end, the numbers game is too much for Goldberg to keep up with. Steiner nails Goldberg with a pipe and locks on the Steiner Recliner. Goldberg is out and Steiner wins the match. I could've done without Russo interfering but yet it still worked._____________________________________________________________________________________________________10.) WCW World Championship Steel Cage Match: Booker T vs Kevin Nash (c)During the time when Nash had some control over booking, he booked himself as WCW World Champion (go figure). The match lasts under 10 minutes and seems more fitted to be a main event for Nitro. Back and forth action with the winner meeting Sting the next night on Nitro. Booker ends up busting Nash open near the end of the match. Booker wins the match with a Book End on Nash to win the title in a decent main event match.Overall: Not a bad Fall Brawl. Most matches delivered although there were a few matches that could've used some improvement in booking and performance. Nonetheless it doesn't take away that overall it was nicely put together PPV. Too bad more WCW PPVs couldn't be that way in its final days
summary: Fall Brawl 2000; One Of WCW's Last Best PPVs
Title: WCW Fall Brawl 1993 VHS

reviewText: Man there are just some things in wrestling that you've just GOTTA have.  This is one of them, no it isn't Rude and Flair, no its not the Stinger or the Stiener, or even the Steamboat, give up??? It's the Shockmaster, the worst idea in the history of WCW.  This tape must be owned as long standing proof of the travisty WCW's creative writers put forth.  Durning the main event the "SHOCKMASTER" who by the way is Tugboat/Typhoon form the WWF bursts threw the a paper projection board (high cost props-WCW only goes for the best you know) and promptly falls down or trips and his mask(a classic star wars storm-trooper helmet covered in glitter) falls off and he scurries to get it before it rolls off the ramp.  He puts it back on and even Jesse the body can't help but make a comment about the fumble.  And then he gets up and points at the ring and a prerecorded message yells something that starts in-"YOUUUUUUU!!!" and ends with "SHOCKMASTER!!!!"  I never got past this part I just couldn't stop laughing.  Buy this for this alone.
summary: WHY FIVE, WELL ITS NOT THE WRESTLING THATS FOR SURE.
Title: WCW Fall Brawl 1993 VHS
